lein''' (born June 25, 1985)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/ethan_edward_klein_born_1985_16902408 |title=Archived copy |access-date=May 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514170600/https://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/ethan_edward_klein_born_1985_16902408 |archive-date=May 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and '''Hila Klein''', ([[Name at birth|n\u00e9e]] '''Hakmon'''; born December 12, 1987). The name h3h3 was initially supposed to be \"HEHE\" due to the couple's initials, but as the username was already taken, they instead opted for h3h3. Their content mostly consists of [[reaction video]]s and [[sketch comedy]] in which they [[Satire|satirize]] [[Cyberculture|internet culture]].\n\nIn addition to their main channel, the Kleins also run a secondary [[vlog]] channel called \"Ethan and Hila\" and a third channel devoted to the H3 [[Podcast]], which features Ethan and Hila interviewing celebrities and [[YouTuber]]s, discussing recent events and sharing [[internet meme|memes]], with a focus on [[internet culture]]. Episodes of the podcast were originally streamed live on [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] and later uploaded to [[YouTube]] in full, but newer episodes are [[Live streamed|live-streamed]] on the podcast's YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|title=The H3 Podcast with Ethan and Hila|url=https://socialblade.com/twitch/user/h3h3productions|website=Social Blade|accessdate=January 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107181018/https://socialblade.com/twitch/user/h3h3productions|archive-date=January 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==YouTube career==\nThe h3h3Productions YouTube channel was created on April 29, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/h3h3productions|title=h3h3Productions YouTube Stats|website=SocialBlade|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113075725/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/h3h3productions|archive-date=November 13, 2018|access-date=November 12, 2018}}</ref>  Their first reaction video was released in November 2013. Many of their early videos were projects for Hila during her time at college. At the time, the couple lived together in Israel, in the [[Florentin, Tel Aviv|Florentin]] neighborhood of [[Tel Aviv]].<ref name=\"Rich\" /> \n\nThe main form of content on the channel is the \"h3h3 reaction video\" series. More involved than traditional [[reaction video]]s, these consist of clips of a source video intermixed with commentary and absurd sketches, a style which has been described as a cross between the works of comedy duo [[Tim & Eric]] and the television series ''[[Mystery Science Theater 3000]].''<ref name=\"Rich\" />\n\nThe channel has gained a reputation for criticizing certain Internet trends and personalities<ref name=\"Klima\" /> as well as the policies of YouTube itself.<ref name=\"Hathaway\" /><ref name=\"Tamburro\" /><ref name=\"Freeman\" /> Often the pair will comment on or participate in online controversies, for instance with SoFloAntonio and prank videos.<ref name=\"Hathaway\" /> Many of these controversies are related to [[outrage culture]], which a playlist on the channel refers to as a \"Cult of Outrage.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjrhosP-Fp_pCQ5XGffN9STbE2QOZwECh|title=Goofing on Triggered Cult of Outrage \u2013 YouTube|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2018-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170528103847/https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjrhosP-Fp_pCQ5XGffN9STbE2QOZwECh|archive-date=May 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn March 21, 2016, h3h3 uploaded \"VAPE NATION,\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Citation|last=h3h3Productions|title=VAPE NATION|date=2016-03-21|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dkm8Hteeh6M|accessdate=2018-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121045230/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dkm8Hteeh6M|archive-date=January 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> a video poking fun at [[Electronic cigarette#Society and culture|vaping culture]] where Ethan buys an [[electronic cigarette]] and smokes it in public, at one point stopping in front of the [[WABC-TV|WABC-TV Eyewitness News]] set. WABC anchor [[Bill Ritter (journalist)|Bill Ritter]] tweeted about Ethan that day, saying \"i got 'blessed' ?  i got vaped? i'm not sure what i got. but i got something. got got?  thanks, i guess.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/billritter7/status/712080570499653633|title=Vaping exchange|last=Ritter|first=Bill|date=<!--5:56 PM - -->21 March 2016|website=@billritter7|accessdate=2018-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325122813/https://twitter.com/billritter7/status/712080570499653633|archive-date=March 25, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> The video would receive over 25 million views by June 2019, and is the most viewed video on the channel.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn July 15, 2016, after winning a [[WQHT|Hot 97]] contest, Ethan met [[DJ Khaled]] and showed him a series of videos, including \"The DJ Khaled Documentary.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Asarch|first1=Steven|title=Two Internet Legends Finally Meet: H3H3 Productions And DJ Khaled|url=http://www.idigitaltimes.com/two-internet-legends-finally-meet-h3h3-productions-and-dj-khaled-545889|accessdate=July 27, 2016|date=July 16, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720102732/http://www.idigitaltimes.com/two-internet-legends-finally-meet-h3h3-productions-and-dj-khaled-545889|archive-date=July 20, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Later, the channel released a short documentary on ''[[Counter-Strike: Global Offensive]]'' gambling, which involves [[Skin gambling|trading skins]] for real-world currency. The channel criticized several YouTubers for attempting to attract young viewers to their gambling websites.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gameranx.com/updates/id/63014/article/csgo-gambling-takes-a-bad-turn/|title=h3h3productions Exposes the Dark Side of CS:GO Gambling|date=July 4, 2016|language=en-US|access-date=July 30, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803184318/http://gameranx.com/updates/id/63014/article/csgo-gambling-takes-a-bad-turn/|archive-date=August 3, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe channel joined the Freedom! network after leaving Collective Digital Studio in August 2015, and since 2016 is a part of the Omnia Media network.{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n==H3 Podcast==\n\nIn 2016, Ethan and Hila launched the H3 Podcast. The first episode, in which they interview [[Justin Roiland]], the co-creator of adult animated science fiction sitcom ''[[Rick and Morty]]'', was released on December 20, 2016.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7196742/|title=IMDB \u2013 H3 Podcast|date=December 20, 2016|language=en-US|access-date=July 18, 2018}}</ref> The episodes were originally streamed live on [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] and later uploaded to YouTube in full, but newer episodes are live streamed on the podcast's YouTube channel. A separate YouTube channel was created for the podcasts after the first few episodes aired, hosting reuploads of the Twitch VODs of older episodes and live-streams of newer ones. In order to combat [[freebooting]], the Kleins created another channel for episode highlights. Although most episodes feature a special guest, some episodes, called \"Top of the Week\" (originally \"Top of the Month\" before the podcast switched to a bi-weekly format<ref name=\"youtube.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9U9TJ4W26k|title=H3 Podcast #10 \u2013 Talking About Jake Paul, Lance Stewart, Jerry Seinfeld (Top Of The Month)|date=June 13, 2017|language=en-US|access-date=March 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815110206/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9U9TJ4W26k|archive-date=August 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=H3 Podcast|title=H3 Podcast #21 \u2013 Was Joey Salads at the Rally? & Elon vs. Zuckerberg (Top Of The Week)|date=2017-08-17|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MBZC4FxMQ_E|accessdate=2018-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171004032129/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MBZC4FxMQ_E|archive-date=October 4, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>) feature only Ethan and Hila. Notable guests so far have included [[PewDiePie]], [[Joji (musician)|Joji]], [[Philip DeFranco]], [[JonTron]], [[Jordan Peterson]], [[Justin Roiland]], [[Alan Melikdjanian|Captain Disillusion]], [[Steve-O]], [[Oliver Tree]], [[Bob Saget]], [[Ninja (streamer)|Ninja]], [[Dr DisRespect]], [[Chris D'Elia]], [[Jake Paul]], [[Bo Burnham]], [[Post Malone]], [[Bill Burr]], [[Jack Black]] and [[Kyle Gass]] of the band [[Tenacious D]], [[Boogie2988]], [[Tim Heidecker]], [[MrBeast]], [[Christina Pazsitzky]], [[Tom Segura]], [[Logic (rapper)|Logic]], [[Casey Neistat]], [[Andrew Yang]], and [[Videogamedunkey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCLtREJY21xRfCuEKvdki1Kw|title=H3 Podcast|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2019-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614183008/https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCLtREJY21xRfCuEKvdki1Kw|archive-date=June 14, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\nFrom September 5 to September 12, 2017, Ethan and Hila, along with [[Justin Roiland]], [[Alex Hirsch]], [[The Owl House (TV series)#Dana Terrace|Dana Terrace]] and [[YouTube]] [[practical joke|prankster]] [[Joey Salads]], raised over [[United States dollar|US]] $200,000 in donations to [[Direct Relief]] for relief efforts in [[Houston]], [[Texas]], in the aftermath of [[Hurricane Harvey]], which caused massive damage to the city.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2017/09/06/h3h3productions-twitch-live-stream-harvey/ |title=H3h3productions Raises Over $100,000 With Twitch Live Stream To Support Hurricane Harvey Relief |last=Gutelle |first=Sam |date=6 September 2017 |website=tubefilter.com |publisher=Tubefilter |access-date=10 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910084025/http://www.tubefilter.com/2017/09/06/h3h3productions-twitch-live-stream-harvey/ |archive-date=September 10, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nEthan and Hila also appear in a character pack for ''[[Payday 2]]'' titled \"h3h3 Character Pack\". Although originally appearing as an [[April Fools]] joke, the character pack was later confirmed for an actual release. The profits from the pack sales are donated directly to the Kleins, helping them with their [[h3h3productions#Hosseinzadeh v. Klein|legal fees]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/payday-2-makers-donate-dlc-profits-to-help-big-youtuber-1795126319|title=Payday 2 Makers Donate DLC Profits To Help Big YouTubers Fight Legal Battle|publisher=[[Kotaku]]|date=2017-11-05|accessdate=2017-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127003736/https://kotaku.com/payday-2-makers-donate-dlc-profits-to-help-big-youtuber-1795126319|archive-date=November 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Hila Klein founded Teddy Fresh,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/10/25/hila-klein-h3h3-productions-teddy-fresh/|website=www.tubefilter.com|title=Hila Klein Of h3h3Productions Launches Her Teddy Fresh Fashion Line|access-date=2019-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207030119/https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/10/25/hila-klein-h3h3-productions-teddy-fresh/|archive-date=February 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> a clothing brand featuring brightly-colored color-blocked beanies, socks, sweatshirts and the iconic teddy bear logo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://teddyfresh.com/|title=Teddy Fresh Official|last=Fresh|first=Teddy|website=Teddy Fresh|language=en|access-date=2019-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190208174316/https://teddyfresh.com/|archive-date=February 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> They did a collaboration with brand Ripndip, which landed them in [[Zumiez]] stores.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zumiez.com/brands/teddy-fresh.html|title=Teddy Fresh Clothing {{!}} Zumiez|website=www.zumiez.com|access-date=2019-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207015738/https://www.zumiez.com/brands/teddy-fresh.html|archive-date=February 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2018, h3h3Productions released a game on the [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]] and [[Google Play]] called \"H3H3: Ball Rider\". The game was developed by Outerminds and features many references to some of their most well-known videos.<ref>{{Citation|last=h3h3Productions|title=H3H3 BALL RIDER|date=2018-09-06|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JN7qaeiRq8U|access-date=2018-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180917045450/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JN7qaeiRq8U|archive-date=September 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Ethan Klein (cropped).jpg|thumb|Ethan Klein visiting Stockholm in 2017|alt=|left]]\nEthan Edward Klein (born June 25, 1985) was born in [[Ventura, California]], to an [[Ashkenazi Jews|Ashkenazi Jewish]] family. His parents are Gary and Donna Klein, and he attended [[Buena High School (California)|Buena High School]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.keyt.com/news/youtuber-star-from-ventura-fighting-copyright-infringement-lawsuit/39875152|title=YouTuber Star From Ventura Fighting Copyright Infringement Lawsuit|website=KEYT-TV|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604134105/http://www.keyt.com/news/youtuber-star-from-ventura-fighting-copyright-infringement-lawsuit/39875152|archive-date=June 4, 2016|access-date=June 4, 2016}}</ref> Ethan studied English Literature at the [[University of California, Santa Cruz]] from 2004 to 2009, and he graduated with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree in creative writing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://puzzups.com/ethan-klein-family-career-lovely-shy-wife-know-internet-entertainers-life/|title=Ethan Klein \u2013 his family, career and his lovely but shy wife! Know about this internet entertainer\u2019s life here!|last=Brooks|first=May|date=July 23, 2017|website=Puzzups|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180416012155/https://puzzups.com/ethan-klein-family-career-lovely-shy-wife-know-internet-entertainers-life/|archive-date=April 16, 2018|access-date=April 15, 2018}}</ref> His paternal grandfather was film and television producer [[Leonard Katzman]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nEP_YdWei0Y|title=H3 Podcast #11 \u2013 Ethan's Parents|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827095341/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nEP_YdWei0Y|archive-date=August 27, 2017|access-date=October 22, 2017}}</ref> He has stated that he has a mild form of [[Tourette syndrome]] and attributes the noticeable twitch of his eyebrows to this.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mde1j-j-GUs|title=What's with Ethan's Eyebrows?!|author=h3h3Productions|date=February 26, 2016|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225020951/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mde1j-j-GUs|archive-date=February 25, 2017|access-date=December 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\nHila Klein ({{nee|Hakmon}}; {{lang-he-n|\u05d4\u05d9\u05dc\u05d4 \u05d7\u05db\u05de\u05d5\u05df}}; born December 12, 1987) was born in [[Holon, Israel]] to a [[Sephardic Jews|Sephardic Jewish]] family. Her father, Yochanan Hakmon, was of Libyan-Jewish descent, whereas her mother is of Turkish-Jewish descent.<ref name=\"hilasdad\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CxN3kQLsfzw|title=Hila's Dad Approves|author=h3h3Productions|date=January 16, 2017|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170124221806/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CxN3kQLsfzw|archive-date=January 24, 2017|access-date=January 16, 2017}}</ref> Hila served as a soldier in the [[Israel Defense Forces]] for two years. During her military service, she met Ethan Klein while he was visiting the [[Yad Vashem|Holocaust Museum]] in [[Jerusalem]] at the time on his [[Birthright Israel]] trip.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ec1syKOdlwo|title=How We Met At The Holocaust Museum|author=h3h3Productions|date=May 17, 2017|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009214451/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ec1syKOdlwo|archive-date=October 9, 2017|access-date=October 10, 2017}}</ref> She then attended the [[Shenkar College of Engineering and Design]] in Israel, but did not complete her studies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cargocollective.com/Shenkart2014/8132028|title=Graduates of the multidisciplinary art department 2014|website=Cargo Collective|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808201920/http://cargocollective.com/Shenkart2014/8132028|archive-date=August 8, 2017|access-date=April 14, 2017}}</ref> Hila became a [[naturalized U.S. citizen]] in September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/HilaKleinH3/status/1173687219736862720|title=I'm a citizen now!! \ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf2\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd\ud83d\uddfd|author=HilaKleinH3|date=September 24, 2019|website=[[Twitter]]|access-date=September 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter several years together, the couple married in 2012. During the early years of the channel, the couple lived together in Israel, in the [[Florentin, Tel Aviv|Florentin]] neighborhood of [[Tel Aviv]].<ref name=\"Rich\" /> In April 2015, the Kleins moved to the United States.<ref name=\"Cya Israel\" /> They first lived in [[Los Angeles]]<ref name=\"Klein, Hila\" /> but moved to [[New York City]] in September 2015.<ref name=\"NYC\" /> They moved back to Los Angeles in August 2016.<ref name=\"Bye NYC\" /> Even though they celebrate Jewish holidays, both of them identify as [[agnostic atheism|agnostic atheists]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sl1c1EdJNz0|title=We Google Ourselves|author=Ethan and Hila|date=April 17, 2016|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501060850/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sl1c1EdJNz0|archive-date=May 1, 2019|access-date=May 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe couple own two [[Yorkshire terrier]]s, one named Shredder<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.twitter.com/h3h3productions/status/937163962562441216|title=Look how tiny he is oh Lord|author=h3h3Productions|date=December 3, 2017|website=[[Twitter]]|access-date=December 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bm1PEsnD4ZF/|title=This is how shredder sleeps every night. This is everything I care about in one photo, my life & heart. The simple essence of what makes\u2026|author=h3h3Productions|website=[[Instagram]]|access-date=December 10, 2018}}</ref> who appears regularly in their videos, and recently Alfredo<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/h3h3productions/status/1171145771221041153|title=The little white boy is our new doggie, Alfredo.}}</ref> who is a rescue. In October 2018, the couple announced that they were expecting their first child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-cGd4ggrKRk|title=Hila is Pregnant \u2013 H3 Podcast Highlights|date=October 5, 2018|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006211728/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-cGd4ggrKRk|archive-date=October 6, 2018|access-date=October 8, 2018}}</ref> In January 2019, the couple announced that their first child is a boy and will be named Theodore Yochanan Klein, in dedication to Hila's father Yochanan who died in July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cylt4QXHuaI|title=Baby Gender Reveal!!|last=Ethan and Hila|date=January 30, 2019|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130211706/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cylt4QXHuaI|archive-date=January 30, 2019|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref> Theodore was born on June 4, 2019.<ref>{{cite podcast|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kP8ho4WL0mU&t=124|first=Ethan|last=Klein|title=The Birth Of Our Son Theodore|website=H3 Podcast|series=#120|time=2:04|publisher=[[YouTube]]|quote=Theodore was born on the 4th at 9 PM ... 9:02PM.|date=June 7, 2019|access-date=June 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Ojomu|first=Nola|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/06/05/youtuber-duo-h3h3-announce-birth-of-their-baby-boy-theodore-9831506/|title=YouTuber duo H3H3 announce birth of their baby boy, Theodore|date=June 5, 2019|newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|access-date=June 5, 2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606023123/https://metro.co.uk/2019/06/05/youtuber-duo-h3h3-announce-birth-of-their-baby-boy-theodore-9831506/|archive-date=June 6, 2019}}</ref> \n\n=== Politics ===\nIn August 2019, Ethan came out in support of 2020 Democratic presidential candidate [[Andrew Yang]], whose platform revolves around the impact of technological development and automation on job displacement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/h3h3productions/status/1160296503308505090|title=Confirmed|author=h3h3Productions|date=August 11, 2019|website=[[Twitter]]|access-date=August 12, 2019}}</ref> Following Andrew Yang's dropout from the 2020 Democratic race, Ethan proceeded to endorse presidential candidate [[Bernie Sanders]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/h3h3productions/status/1227412195677356032|title=I am officially endorsing @BernieSanders for president with a $1,000 donation. Although take my endorsement with a grain of salt because my qualification is that I talk about poop on a podcast all day. That being said, I do support Bernie and wish him good luck.pic.twitter.com/2MLlFqQgOo|last=Klein|first=Ethan|date=2020-02-11|website=@h3h3productions|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n=== ''Hosseinzadeh v. Klein'' ===\nIn April 2016, Matt Hosseinzadeh ({{lang-fa|\u0645\u062a \u062d\u0633\u06cc\u0646 \u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647}}; born August 19, 1977), an Iranian-American YouTuber who goes by \"MattHossZone\" and \"Bold Guy\", filed a [[civil action]] against the Kleins for copyright infringement.<ref>https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B5TuLsugW1h8WHVrSTFTenVtOTg/view</ref> h3h3Productions made a reaction video to Hosseinzadeh's video \"Bold Guy vs. Parkour Girl\". Hosseinzadeh claims that he initially contacted the Kleins \"to politely ask them to remove my content from their video\", but that they refused. Hosseinzadeh's lawyer, Tim Bukher, claims that the video used more than 70% of his work \"while contributing nothing substantive to it.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/h3h3-ethan-hila-matthoss-lawsuit-1201784349/|title=Legal Fund for YouTube's H3H3 Raises More Than $145,000 to Fight MattHoss Copyright Lawsuit|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=May 27, 2016|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=May 31, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729181518/http://variety.com/2016/digital/news/h3h3-ethan-hila-matthoss-lawsuit-1201784349/|archive-date=July 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/amp/entertainment/youtube-stars-matt-hoss-h3h3-copyright-battle-bold-guy-article-1.2656345#|title=YouTube stars Matt Hoss, h3h3 in copyright battle over 'Bold Guy' \u2013 NY Daily News|website=www.nydailynews.com|access-date=June 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604062545/http://www.nydailynews.com/amp/entertainment/youtube-stars-matt-hoss-h3h3-copyright-battle-bold-guy-article-1.2656345|archive-date=June 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keyt.com/news/local-news/youtuber-star-from-ventura-fighting-copyright-infringement-lawsuit/87627559|title=YouTuber Star From Ventura Fighting Copyright Infringement Lawsuit|first=Kelsey|last=Gerckens|date=June 3, 2016|access-date=May 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729173349/http://www.keyt.com/news/local-news/youtuber-star-from-ventura-fighting-copyright-infringement-lawsuit/87627559|archive-date=July 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter a video on this was released by h3h3Productions the following month, fellow YouTube personality [[Philip DeFranco]] started a fundraiser on [[GoFundMe]] to help raise money for their legal fees, citing the need to protect fair use on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/3134227/youtube-war-philip-defrancos-gofundme-raises-60000-as-bold-guy-matt-hoss-sues-ethan-and-hila-of-h3h3/|title=YouTube War: Philip DeFranco's GoFundMe Raises $60,000 As 'Bold Guy' Matt 'Hoss' Sues Ethan And Hila Of H3H3|website=The Inquisitr News|access-date=May 26, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729175714/http://www.inquisitr.com/3134227/youtube-war-philip-defrancos-gofundme-raises-60000-as-bold-guy-matt-hoss-sues-ethan-and-hila-of-h3h3/|archive-date=July 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The fundraiser raised almost $170,000, receiving large donations from notable individuals including [[Fine Brothers]], [[Markus Persson|Markus \"Notch\" Persson]], [[PewDiePie]], [[Markiplier]], [[Jacksepticeye]], [[Justin Roiland]], and [[Garry Newman]]. On May 26, 2016, Ethan and Hila announced that the funds raised will go into an [[escrow account]] called the \"Fair Use Protection Account\" (FUPA), overseen by Morrison & Lee LLP to be used to help people defend fair use.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/4349864/ethan-klein-h3h3productions-fair-use-protection-account-fupa/|title=This YouTube Star Got Sued, Raised $130,000, and Wants to Change the Site Forever|last=Chan|first=Melissa|website=TIME.com|access-date=May 28, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160527194308/http://time.com/4349864/ethan-klein-h3h3productions-fair-use-protection-account-fupa/|archive-date=May 27, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 27, 2016, Lee announced on Twitter that he had filed a motion to dismiss the lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GeekAttorney/status/747545139770494977|title=Michael Lee on Twitter|website=Twitter|access-date=July 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170607153957/https://twitter.com/GeekAttorney/status/747545139770494977|archive-date=June 7, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCourt filings from November 2016 state that Ethan and Hila Klein had new attorneys and were no longer represented by Morrison & Lee LLP.<ref>{{cite web|url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=SUahTUQ4WMw|title=Matt Hoss & h3h3: It's complicated|last=Leonard French|date=January 25, 2017|via=YouTube|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011002311/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SUahTUQ4WMw|archive-date=October 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Later claims by both Ethan and Hila that the switch was due to among other reasons, \"things not working out\". They also discussed that the alleged fees charged by the new firm were US$54,146.57 for one month of work. There is currently no evidence that Morrison & Lee LLP had ever controlled the funds raised by H3h3Productions, and Morrison & Lee LLP has not confirmed the allegation.<ref name=\"lawsuitmoney\">{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m40bWgWH8Ro|title=We're Still Being Sued|date=February 27, 2017|publisher=[[YouTube]]|access-date=February 27, 2017|people=h3h3 Productions|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707144547/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m40bWgWH8Ro|archive-date=July 7, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 17, 2017, the trial set for April 17, 2017 was adjourned in anticipation of ruling on [[summary judgment]] motions.<ref>{{Citation|last=Leonard French|title=h3h3 Poker: the Judge shows Her Hand|date=March 17, 2017|url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=t7K387y1Lo8|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn August 23, 2017, Ethan tweeted that they won the lawsuit.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=h3h3productions |number=900412107434319872|date=August 23, 2017|title=We won the lawsuit. Video coming soon. Huge victory for fair use on YouTube.}}</ref> In her decision in favor of Ethan and Hila, U.S. District Judge [[Katherine B. Forrest]] ruled that the Kleins' commentary video constituted \"[[fair use]] as a matter of law\", describing it as \"quintessential comment and criticism.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/08/23/judge-sides-with-youtubers-ethan-and-hila-klein-in-copyright-lawsuit/|title=Judge sides with YouTubers Ethan and Hila Klein in copyright lawsuit|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|last=Ha|first=Anthony|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825000209/https://techcrunch.com/2017/08/23/judge-sides-with-youtubers-ethan-and-hila-klein-in-copyright-lawsuit/|archive-date=August 25, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.courtlistener.com/docket/4356997/hosseinzadeh-v-klein/#entry-116|title=Docket for Hosseinzadeh v. Klein -     CourtListener.com|website=CourtListener|language=en|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827012617/https://www.courtlistener.com/docket/4356997/hosseinzadeh-v-klein/#entry-116|archive-date=August 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Allegations against ''The Wall Street Journal''===\nH3h3Productions, alongside several other channels, supported YouTube personality [[PewDiePie]] amid a 2017 controversy over [[PewDiePie#Media controversies, streaming, and formatted shows (2017\u22122018)|Nazi jokes in one of his videos]] from January.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thoughtcatalog.com/jeff-markum/2017/02/pewdiepie-just-responded-to-claims-of-anti-semitism-on-youtube-and-its-pretty-intense/|title=PewDiePie just responded to claims of anti-Semitism on YouTube and it's pretty intense|first=Jeff|last=Markum|publisher=Thought Catalog|date=February 16, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516163304/http://thoughtcatalog.com/jeff-markum/2017/02/pewdiepie-just-responded-to-claims-of-anti-semitism-on-youtube-and-its-pretty-intense/|archive-date=May 16, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On February 14, ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' ran a story about PewDiePie's previous references to [[Adolf Hitler]], which brought nine other videos into the debate and elicited frequent discussions on whether they were taken out of context.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/the-pewdiepie-fiasco-one-month-later-1793308126|title=The PewDiePie Fiasco, One Month Later|first=Patricia|last=Hernandez|publisher=Kotaku|date=March 24, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817054348/http://kotaku.com/the-pewdiepie-fiasco-one-month-later-1793308126|archive-date=August 17, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> When YouTube subsequently released advertiser-friendly tools to help companies avoid offensive videos, Ethan Klein claimed that the tools were overly broad and negatively affected unrelated content, including his own channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://adage.com/article/digital/youtube-feels-ad-squeeze-creators/308489/|title=As YouTube tinkers with ad formula, its stars see their videos lose money|first=Garett|last=Sloane|publisher=Advertising Age|date=March 30, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803125626/http://adage.com/article/digital/youtube-feels-ad-squeeze-creators/308489/|archive-date=August 3, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOne of the authors of the ''Wall Street Journal'' piece, Jack Nicas, wrote another article on March 24, claiming that YouTube did not do a good enough job of keeping major advertisements away from racist content. Klein accused the report of being written selectively to maximize outrage. Specifically, the article showed a [[Coca-Cola]] ad playing on a video of the country song \"Alabama Nigger\" by American white supremacist [[Johnny Rebel (singer)|Johnny Rebel]]. Upon seeing that the video was not contributing to the uploader's income, Klein alleged that Nicas had used an altered screenshot and asserted this in a video. Hours later, he was informed that the video was indeed monetized, but through a [[YouTube#Revenue to copyright holders|copyright claim]] rather than an explicit choice of the user. Klein withdrew his accusation in response and ''The Wall Street Journal'' released a statement that it stood by the authenticity of the screenshots.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heatst.com/culture-wars/youtube-powerhouse-h3h3-retracts-video-accusing-wall-street-journal-of-falsifying-evidence/|title=YouTube Powerhouse H3H3 Retracts Video Accusing Wall Street Journal of Falsifying Evidence|first=Joe|last=Simonson|publisher=Heat St|date=April 3, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414163920/https://heatst.com/culture-wars/youtube-powerhouse-h3h3-retracts-video-accusing-wall-street-journal-of-falsifying-evidence/|archive-date=April 14, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Rich\">{{cite news|author=Rich, Jacob|date=February 25, 2016|url=https://www.michigandaily.com/section/arts/b-side-why-world-needs-h3h3productions|title=Why the world needs h3h3 Productions|work=The Michigan Daily|accessdate=February 26, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160226102558/https://www.michigandaily.com/section/arts/b-side-why-world-needs-h3h3productions|archive-date=February 26, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Klima\">{{cite web|author=Klima, Jeff|date=July 31, 2015|url=http://newmediarockstars.com/2015/07/is-h3h3-productions-the-most-negative-channel-on-youtube/|title=Is h3h3 Productions the Most Negative Channel on YouTube?|work=New Media Rockstars|accessdate=February 26, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708170338/http://newmediarockstars.com/2015/07/is-h3h3-productions-the-most-negative-channel-on-youtube/|archive-date=July 8, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Hathaway\">{{cite web|author=Hathaway, Jay|date=F